metadata.name: Caracas Early and Colorful Postcards of an Abstract National Prize of Architecture
metadata.description:
This is part of the collection "Caracas Early and Colorful Postcards, My Early Days", photographs of the first years of the venezuelan photographer Azalia Licón documenting Caracas, looking for its colors, trying to make sense of one of the most dangerous cities of the world and also its contradictions.

The whole collection is a historical document of an ever changing Latin American city.
